messages.content: ComfyUI Sokes Nodes is a small node suite for ComfyUI that includes nodes such as Current Date with Custom Formatting and Empty Latent Selector (9 Inputs).
What is the purpose of the Current Date with Custom Formatting node in ComfyUI Sokes Nodes?
The Current Date with Custom Formatting node in ComfyUI Sokes Nodes is useful for file saving organization, allowing custom date formatting such as YYYY-MM-DD.
What is the function of the Empty Latent Selector (9 Inputs) node in ComfyUI Sokes Nodes?
The Empty Latent Selector (9 Inputs) node in ComfyUI Sokes Nodes is useful for exporting a random latent dimensions based on a fixed set.
How can you install ComfyUI Sokes Nodes?
To install ComfyUI Sokes Nodes, open a terminal, navigate to the ComfyUI/custom_nodes/ directory, run the command 'git clone https://github.com/m-sokes/ComfyUI-Sokes-Nodes.git', and restart ComfyUI.
ComfyUI is a node-based backend and GUI for Stable Diffusion.
What is the recommended extension for ComfyUI?
The recommended extension for ComfyUI is ComfyUI-Manager.
What is a potential future node concept mentioned for ComfyUI Sokes Nodes?
A potential future node concept mentioned for ComfyUI Sokes Nodes is an SDXL Prompt Styler node with custom categories based on JSON file(s).
